rides.name: Air Jumbo
rides.description: Take flight with the most unlikely co-pilots, baby elephants, on this light-hearted float-around.

seasonal.name: Air Jumbo
seasonal.description: These perky, happy, junior elephants may not have wings, but they love to fly with their giant ears. Each one has a different brightly-colored saddle. Choose your favorite little pachyderm and then climb inside, as it starts to spin around a circus top in the center.

rides.name: Air Safari
rides.description: High flying adventure awaits pilots in training as their planes lift off for a rousing roundabout in the air.

rides.name: BATMAN™: The Ride
rides.description: The superhero takes you on a menacing ride of relentless loops and twists.

seasonal.name: BATMAN The Ride
seasonal.description:
Something dark is happening in GOTHAM CITY and the caped crusader needs your help!

BATMAN: The Ride will show you what it feels like to be the ultimate caped crusader, on this intense 50 mile-per-hour monster that is definitely not for the timid. Step through the tall carved gates of Bruce Wayne’s haunted manor. You’ll journey deep into the bat cave, surrounded by the flying creatures of the night.

The steel inverted beast you are about to board will blast you off into the sky over GOTHAM to give you the perfect vantage point over the deadly criminals throughout the city. As you load into your chair hanging from an overhead track, note that you’re about to fight crime with your feet just dangling free through the fog. Following a 10-story lift hill to the top of the world, brace yourself for a terrifying 360-degree loop right off the bat. Warming up is for the feint hearted and fear is not something you can bring with you when traveling as the Dark Knight.

If you survive this terrifying night, you’ll have faced a mind-warping five inversions. Now watch the ground under your dangling feet whip around as the screaming city below flips over and over, through a tightly packed series of gravity-defying twists that will grind you into submission just like the murderous criminals and monsters of GOTHAM CITY.

Minimum height requirement: 54″ to ride

seasonal.name: BATMAN The Ride
seasonal.description: BATMAN never gets a day off and Christmas time is no exception! Get ready to ride with BATMAN himself and fight crime. Experience drops, 50 MPH speeds, Zero-G rolls and 360 degree loops that only a holiday master like yourself can accomplish! The villains of Gotham don’t stand a chance against you!

rides.name: Big Wheel
rides.description: Ride the enduring classic Ferris wheel.  At 150 feet, this one’s as big as the sky.

seasonal.name: Big Wheel
seasonal.description: Step into your very own bucket and fly through Six Flags on your way to the North Pole! Be sure to look around you on your journey and take in the beautiful holiday lights!

rides.name: BIZARRO™
rides.description: Dare to defeat the multiple lunatic loops, demented drops, ridiculous rolls, and crazed corkscrews.

seasonal.name: BIZARRO
seasonal.description:
What if a super hero had all the power of SUPERMAN, but decided to use it for evil because Fright Fest brings out the worst in people? Welcome to the twisted world of BIZARRO, SUPERMAN’s dark evil twin. With seven relentless inversions—the most you’ll find in the entire park—let’s see if you can face up to this dangerous and demented foe through the darkness and the fog.

3,985 feet is a lot of track, and plenty of time for you to get to know BIZARRO and the backward “S” stamped on his chest. You’ll see every inch of that track because you’ll be taking this one floorless, with your feet just dangling in the air.

BIZARRO hasn’t got the charm part of being a super hero down yet, he just bluntly cuts right to the action. Let’s kick things off with a 132-foot drop. Then BIZARRO will shoot you through a terrifying tunnel of white mist, in the shape of his stolen SUPERMAN shield.

Listen closely to the killer sound design pumping into your ear, then brace yourself because you’re in for one of the tallest vertical loops in the world—a whopping 114 feet. At least BIZARRO is ambitious. This is followed immediately by a dreaded dive loop and a zero G roll. Watch out for the explosions of fire going off right in your face! At 60 miles per hour and taking as much as 4 Gs, you’re probably starting to figure out what it feels like to have super hero strength, both with and without gravity.

Now it’s time to fly into a cobra roll, a double-inversion that forms the shape of a snake head, spitting you back out even faster in the same direction you started. But tell that villain you’ve got some moves of your own by now, darting towards the insane finish with a hellacious helix, a couple of interlocking corkscrews, and a sick hammerhead turn, as fast as a speeding zombie!

Minimum height requirement: 54″ to ride

rides.name: HARLEY QUINN™ Crazy Train
rides.description: Family thrills await on this swift and scenic junior roller coaster that races through the hills at 22 mph.

seasonal.name: HARLEY QUINN™ Crazy Train
seasonal.description: Take a ride on this family-style coaster beneath the twinkling lights of the Holly Jolly Christmas section!

rides.name: Carousel
rides.description: Step back in time and choose your ride on this restored old time classic carousel, a favorite for all ages.

seasonal.name: Carousel
seasonal.description: For generations, the carousel has been one of the most magical and cherished rides for young and old alike and now it will be the crowned jewel of Holiday In The Park! This carousel is decorated with dancing lights and a giant gingerbread cookie.

rides.name: Congo Rapids
rides.description: Brave the current on the ultimate white-water river rafting experience!

rides.name: Daffy Hot Air Balloons
rides.description: Whirl through the sky on Daffy Duck’s revolving hot air balloon jamboree.

rides.name: Dare Devil Dive
rides.description: Plummet 15.5 stories through the air at 60 mph for the ultimate skydiving experience! Additional fee required.

seasonal.name: Dare Devil Dive
seasonal.description: Take a delirious leap into extreme exhilaration!

rides.name: Déjà Vu
rides.description: This classic scrambler will spin you so fast you won’t remember if you’re coming or going!

seasonal.name: Deja Vu
seasonal.description: The spinning scrambler will give you Deja Vu to holiday seasons past with warm memories. You’ll spin so fast you won’t remember if you’re coming or going, but you’ll have your family and friends along for the ride!

rides.name: El Toro
rides.description: Classic architecture meets cutting edge engineering

seasonal.name: El Toro
seasonal.description:
Right behind the park — just behind El Toro — is a secret toxic dump.

It’s a place where corrupt businesses dump the toxic waste that they hide from the government.

Animals, both domestic and wild, visit at night and feast on the refuse they find there. The best pickings are found in the crisp nights of autumn.

Snack time changes these animals beyond recognition. They become aggressive and unafraid of humans. Their eyes develop weeping sores that burn, as they stretch a dripping paw toward the sweetest part they can find. Bits of flesh and hair can be seen, caught between their long and flaking claws. Teeth shoot into fangs, while their drooling tongues wipe the slime from their smirking lips.

And, still, they’re hungry.

Hired security patrols the park at night. They’ve reported seeing animals, of some sort, but these crass creatures are so quick and so secretive, who can be sure?

The beasts hunt in packs, trapping their helpless prey in the shadows. They congregate on the edges of the forest behind Shockwave, the better to check out the crowd. Brazenly, they attack riders at the depths of this ride’s descent. Then, bellies still not full, they continue their snacking – long after the vile forces of darkness turn into tenuous morning.

Minimum height requirement: 48″ to ride

rides.name: Enchanted Teacups
rides.description: This tea party’s out of control on a teacup-style spin-a-rama.  The more you twist, the harder you spin!

seasonal.name: Gingerbread Twist
seasonal.description: Twist around on these Christmas cups and get ready to laugh, cheer and spin the night away all holiday season long! A little twist of gingerbread is all you need to go with your tea. Warm your hearts with laughter on our family teacup ride.

rides.name: Fender Benders
rides.description: No need for brakes as you put your pedal to the metal on this classic, clobbering, bumper car smash-up!

seasonal.name: Fender Benders
seasonal.description: It wouldn’t be the holiday rush without some gridlock on your way to do last-minute shopping for loved ones. No need for brakes as you put your pedal to the metal on this classic, clobbering, bumper car smash-up!

rides.name: Foghorn Leghorn Stagecoach Express
rides.description: All aboard classic stagecoaches sized for junior frontiersmen, on this colorful tour through the Wild West.

rides.name: Great American Road Race
rides.description: You’ll love the thrill of the open road on this classic go-kart speedway. Additional fee required.

rides.name: GREEN LANTERN™
rides.description: Stand up for a good time on record-setting heights, inversions, and drops over 4,155 feet of heroic track!

seasonal.name: GREEN LANTERN
seasonal.description:
Stand up to your fear during Fright Fest on GREEN LANTERN.

You won’t believe how smooth this ride is, considering you are flying at 63 miles per hour over zombies of terror—all while standing up. Humans just weren’t designed to move this fast … but super heroes were.

The bright green and yellow track glowing through the fog will lead you on a record-setting journey, smashing all the previous title-holders for height, speed, drops, inversions, length.

It all starts with a 155 foot hill. Now that you’re committed, how about a bravery-crunching 144-foot drop followed immediately by a 121-foot loop? Now you’re starting to feel super! On the blisteringly fast 100 foot diving loop, wave high to SUPERMAN Ultimate Flight next door, but don’t get too friendly because immediately you’ll soon be zooming into an ultra-unique 72-foot inclined loop. The entire vertical loop is tilted at an angle, and you enter it sideways, because super heroes don’t need to fly in straight lines.

Over the 4,155 feet of track, you’ll hug the ground, take crazy corkscrews, and do your best to break the sound barrier over and over again. Surviving Fright Fest is all in a day’s work for GREEN LANTERN!

Minimum height requirement: 48″ to ride

seasonal.name: GREEN LANTERN™
seasonal.description: You'll be standing in awe of the beauty around you. Green lights show you the way to this stand-up steel coaster that will throw you for a loop.

rides.name: Houdini’s Great Escape
rides.description: Don’t get spooked by the ghost of Harry Houdini on this elaborately designed journey into magic.

seasonal.name: Houdini's Great Escape
seasonal.description:
In the mid-1900s, an imposing mansion was built in Jackson by a successful local magician named Roger Manville Strycher.
He was a master of sleight of hand, or prestidigitation, and children loved to see Strycher make coins disappear right before their eyes, only to have them reappear inside their coat pockets.

Approximately 50 years earlier, another magician had gained acclaim – a Hungarian-born illusionist named Harry Houdini. Houdini was best known for his sensational escape acts, finding his way out of chains, shackles, ropes, handcuffs and straitjackets right before people’s eyes. Strycher, believing he was indeed the greatest magician on Earth, vowed to outperform Houdini in anything he tried. In his library, he gathered and studied some of Houdini’s old props and illusions and practiced day and night for what he called the “world’s greatest feat.” If Houdini could make an elephant disappear, Strycher vowed to make it look like child’s play – he was going to levitate and rotate his mansion.

While no one knows exactly what Strycher was doing in the mansion, the townspeople reported hearing loud noises and wailing from inside. Strycher, now obsessed and despondent, canceled his European tour of 1952, instead toiling day and night on his illusion. One stormy night in October of 1956, 20 years after Houdini’s death, Jackson residents heard an unbelievably loud thunder crash followed by what sounded like a crashing freight train. The night had turned so stormy that no one dared venture outside for fear of being swept away by a possible tornado.

In the morning, they emerged from their homes and what they saw left them in utter disbelief. While the entire block looked untouched, exactly as the day before, Strycher’s house was completely upside down. His neighbors frantically looked for him and thought he might be crushed in the rubble somewhere, but his body was never found. The only items seemingly undisturbed were Houdini’s old illusions. The townspeople believed that it was Houdini’s spirit – not Strycher – who made the impossible happen. They whispered that Strycher had attempted to trap and contain Houdini’s spirit; but in death as was in life, nothing could hold him and Houdini made a great escape.

Minimum height requirement: 48″ to ride

seasonal.name: Houdini's Great Escape
seasonal.description: The magic of the holidays is about believing in things you cannot see! Take a unique and supernatural journey through Harry Houdini’s secret escape after taking in the sights of the Peppermint Path.

rides.name: Jolly Roger
rides.description: An enormous creepy skeleton is your host on a delightfully dizzy—making spin—out.

seasonal.name: Jolly Roger
seasonal.description: Just down the path from the Buccaneer pirate ship, the Holly Jolly Roger is a holiday twist on a classic sailing flag, which you might know better as a skull and crossbones! When you see the Jolly Roger, you know pirates are near.

rides.name: Jumpin’ Joey
rides.description: Jiggle till you giggle on this bouncy tower lift for little kids and big kangaroos!

rides.name: Kingda Ka
rides.description: Bolt from 0 to 128 mph in 3.5 seconds to the top of a 456-foot high track.

rides.name: Nitro
rides.description: Ride a mile of ultra slim, ultra fast track over hyper sized loops and twists, including a 21 story drop.

seasonal.name: Nitro
seasonal.description:
A few weeks ago a hole was found next to the entrance of Nitro.

It is said that, every now and then, something scrambles out of this hole and visits us. Huge, slimy tails whip through the night. Sharp points of red-forked fangs flash in the shadows. And, heaven help you, once it clamps onto your leg or creeps inside your jacket.

The creature was recently seen by one of our park watchmen, who described it as, “an octopus, a dragon, and a human caricature…a pulpy, tentacled head surmounted a grotesque scaly body with rudimentary wings” before he burst into tears and began talking in gibberish (he said something like “Ph’nglui mglw’nafh Cthulhu R’lyeh wgah’nagl fhtagn” right before he dropped dead. We have no idea what it means).

Over the last couple of weeks Six Flags has spent a significant amount of money to try to seal the hole. But the ability of this creature to dig his (or her) way out is staggering.

Guests riding Nitro are encouraged to keep a weather eye on the track ahead. Anyone who sees something up ahead with a gigantic, unkempt mouth with dozens of sharp pointy teeth should……pray for it to end quickly…

Minimum height requirement: 54″ to ride

For your safety, no loose articles including cell phones are permitted on Nitro. All loose articles must be secured in a button or zipped pocket, locker or with a non-rider.

seasonal.name: Nitro
seasonal.description: You better not shout, you better not cry! Better not pout and I’m telling you why. Because Nitro is taking you up to the Sky! Santa Claus himself is even a little nervous to take on this giant steel sleigh, as it takes you up 23 stories as you crest the top.

rides.name: Parachute Training Center: Edwards AFB
rides.description: Experience the rush of parachuting from a 250-foot tower, without jumping out of an airplane!

seasonal.name: Parachute Training Center: Edwards AFB
seasonal.description:
Glide to the Ground with Parachute Training!
Ever wonder what it feels like to jump out of an airplane? Well you’re about to get your chance, without the hassle of a pesky take-off and landing.

You and a brave buddy can take a seat under a giant parachute and get hauled straight up to the top of a staggering 250-foot tall tower. Seeing as the only other way to get to that height would be a jet engine or a pair of wings, we thought we’d give you a lift.

The ride up is so smooth you’ll barely notice it—if you don’t look down, that is. You just get whisked to the top, swiftly and silently, darting up through the air to the view of the century! With the whole park beneath you and the great landscape in every direction, enjoy this wonderful sight for a brief moment, because in about three seconds we’ll be pulling the ripcord to send you soaring.

As your parachute billows and fills with air, you’ll float straight back down, gracefully delivered back to solid ground. It turns out skydiving is a lot less stressful than you thought, but just as thrilling.

rides.name: Porky Pig Camp Wagons
rides.description: Take an old west spin on a junior Ferris wheel for little piglets!

rides.name: Raja’s Rickshaws
rides.description: Little legs can take a load off on this scrambler—style rickshaw spinner slowed down to a junior pace.

rides.name: Runaway Mine Train
rides.description: Take off on this authentic, fast-paced trip to the frontier!

rides.name: Skull Mountain
rides.description: Tunnel into a fully immersive world of adventure on this all indoor coaster—in total darkness!

seasonal.name: Skull Mountain
seasonal.description: Tunnel into a fully immersive world of holiday adventure on this all indoor coaster—in total darkness! The lighted beauty of the coaster will prime you for your swift adventure into dips and turns perfect for the whole family this holiday season.

rides.name: SkyScreamer
rides.description: Get a bird's eye view on the startlingly tall 242-foot tower in a 40 mph spin around the top of the world.

seasonal.name: Skyscreamer of Doom
seasonal.description:
Sometimes the inspiration for rides comes from the strangest places.

The SkyScreamer is one such ride. Igor L. Friedman was a Russian immigrant who came to America with hopes that unique inventions would make him rich. He toiled night and day developing outrageous, bizarre and ultimately useless creations. His wife Katarina was frustrated and angry of all the time she felt he wasted on these concoctions, while she was left to raise their newborn alone. Igor assured Katarina that they would live the American dream once he was able to showcase his inventions before a panel of investors on a new reality television show.

But instead, the investors laughed Igor out of the studio and he was left to return home distraught and defeated. Katarina, with disappointment all over her face, asked Igor what their family would do to survive. Igor snapped at her to leave him alone because his next invention would be the one that really “took off.” Inspired by Katarina’s nagging he worked tirelessly on a new “spin” on a baby mobile.

He convinced the judges to visit his warehouse to see his giant new creation. When they entered the hanger-like building he offered them some light refreshments, including a homemade punch, as a thank you for making the trip. As the judges looked around, all they saw was a contraption that looked like meat hooks suspended on chains from a massive pinwheel. Confused, they asked him what the purpose of his invention was. Igor responded, “Just wait and see,” before they immediately became drowsy from something in the punch.

When the judges awoke it was to wind in their faces and sharp, excruciating pains in their shoulders and calves. Looking down, they let out blood-curdling screams realizing in terror that they were swinging and hanging more than 40 feet from the ground. Igor had pierced their flesh with the meat hooks and strung them from the chains. He completed the mobile with his wife Katarina as the final ornament. With his baby sitting silently in his stroller beneath the structure, covered in blood, he had finally proven everyone wrong – his invention was a success.

Minimum height requirement: 44″ to ride with adult 48″ to ride alone

seasonal.name: SkyScreamer
seasonal.description: Get a bird’s eye view of over a million glittering lights on the startlingly tall 242-foot tower. Take in the sights, smells and crisp air while scouting out the next adventure you’ll take. Don’t forget to keep an eye out for Santa and snowflakes while you’re up there!

rides.name: Skyway Frontier Adventures
rides.description: Ride a classic cable car high over the park, from Frontier Adventures to Lakefront.

rides.name: Skyway — Lakefront
rides.description: With these classic cable cars, getting from Lakefront to Frontier Adventures has never been so fun!

seasonal.name: Skyway
seasonal.description: Take a round-trip cable car ride high about the twinkling lights for a reindeer's view! Cable cars load and unload at the station located in Poinsettia Peak.

rides.name: SUPERMAN™: Ultimate Flight
rides.description: Soar the superhero way on this intense flight over utterly innovative loops, twists, and curves at 51mph!

seasonal.name: SUPERMAN: Ultimate Flight
seasonal.description:
SUPERMAN: Ultimate Flight soars above the living dead.

Up in the air, it’s a bird, it’s a plane … or is it a flying demon? This heroically-proportioned 106-foot tall steel champion is not just one of the most creative and insanely designed roller coaster you will ever ride. More importantly, you will get to experience the world through SUPERMAN’s eyes.

Step over the threshold of the giant iconic letter S, and into the world of stupendous speed and effortless fluidity. The red and gold tracks shoot in front of and behind you just like the blur of SUPERMAN’s cape, as you travel at hyper-sonic speeds most humans have never known. The faster the better in an effort to escape the living dead.

You’ll ride the way SUPERMAN flies—face down and head first. This is the ultimate way to experience the challenge of the mind-ripping new legend, the pretzel loop! Once you clear the first ten story drop, you’ll fly into this totally innovative loop design, which is really two inversions in one. You can tell from the name of the pretzel loop that you’ll be more than slightly twisted by this warped track!

Then, with the grace of SUPERMAN, you’ll tackle a high speed horseshoe-shaped curve, a breathtaking helix, and then a full 360-degree in-line roll. Good thing you left your kryptonite at home.

There is a sense of total fluidity and control as you maneuver this track. You’re a pro now, as you sail head first over the razor thin track. You’ll have a wide open view of the world as it blurs past you, while soaring through the air like an adventurous super hero brave enough to conquer Fright Fest.

Minimum height requirement: 54″ to ride

seasonal.name: SUPERMAN: Ultimate Flight
seasonal.description: Seeing is believing when it comes to the magic of the season. Take a spin on SUPERMAN: Ultimate Flight and let the Man of Steel himself show you the magic of flying through the air amidst glittering lights.

rides.name: Swashbuckler
rides.description: Experience the awesome power of gravity on this standing, revolving, adrenaline rush.

seasonal.name: The Haunted Swashbuckler
seasonal.description:
Swashbuckler is the premier residence in the park for angry and disillusioned spirits.

Hovering underneath — for reasons nobody can explain — are the ghosts of those who’ve suffered unspeakable endings from all over the world.

These spirits are lonely, frustrated, and bitter about being left behind. Their mission is to bring others into the mud pit of misery they call home.

From above, they reach out. Their ghoulish touch rips an arm from its socket, with an unnatural jerk and unbearable pain. The vehicle twists and careens, and at each rotation riders disappear, until at the end none are left.

What drives these lost and crazed spirits? Perhaps the thrill of new residents makes their horrible world more bearable. Hopefully, we’ll never know, and we’ll do everything in our power to remain ignorant.

Minimum height requirement: 42″ to ride

seasonal.name: Swashbuckler
seasonal.description: Round and round you go! You’ll be pinned to the side by sheer gravity, like in a giant centrifuge. As the wheel tilts on its axis to 45°, you’ll be spinning wildly out of control, but somehow magically held in your place to take in the blur of holiday lights surrounding you!

rides.name: Tango
rides.description: Jiggle till you giggle on a zigger that skitters back and forth across a twisty course.

rides.name: Tornado
rides.description: Get twisted in knots by this tyke-sized swinging bench ride, for a speedy, spintastic good time.

rides.name: Buccaneer
rides.description: High flying thrills await as the pirate ship Buccaneer sets sail, swing high and low on waves of excitement.

seasonal.name: Buccaneer
seasonal.description: Dashing into the sky on this giant pirate ship is the perfect way to swing to new heights with holiday cheer! High flying thrills await as the pirate ship Buccaneer sets sail, swing high and low on waves of excitement.

rides.name: THE DARK KNIGHT™ Coaster
rides.description: Chase THE JOKER deep underground on GOTHAM’s abandoned subway on this all—indoor steel coaster!

seasonal.name: DARK KNIGHT Coaster
seasonal.description:
It takes a tough hero for a zombie-laden city this rough!

If crime fighting’s his business, THE DARK KNIGHT has plenty of work to keep him busy in the heart of Demon District. And on this all-enclosed indoor thrill coaster with more than 1,200 feet of track, you’ll get your chance to lend a helping hand. If you can outwit THE JOKER, that is!

At Harvey Dent’s press conference, THE JOKER interrupts the proceedings and complete pandemonium breaks loose. You’re evacuated to the GOTHAM CITY subway to make your escape.

Well there’s nothing like a nice little nerve-wracking stroll down into an authentic GOTHAM CITY rail station. As you may know, GOTHAM’s a rough town, and this run-down dilapidated subway station has seen better days. Board a train for a relentless ride through the very dark abandoned subway line, in an elaborately designed cinematic set. It’s covered with graffiti and lit by flickering strobes. If you keep your eyes peeled you just might see THE JOKER or THE DARK KNIGHT himself.

You will face six complete 180 degree turns, and a series of hair-raising ups and down from a height of 45 feet. Ever try that kind of thing in a dark, enclosed space at 30 miles per hour? Now you know why it isn’t easy fighting crime in town like this!

Minimum height requirement: 42″ to ride with adult 48″ to ride alone

seasonal.name: The DARK KNIGHT Coaster
seasonal.description: No one wants to let evil ruin the magical spirit. Join THE DARK KNIGHT to Chase THE JOKER deep underground on GOTHAM’s abandoned subway on this all—indoor steel coaster!

rides.name: Twister
rides.description: This gargantuan top spin classic delivers 360 flips at 4Gs, without the courtesy of a warning.

seasonal.name: The Twister
seasonal.description:
If you want to know the real reason why selfie sticks were banned from park property, you’re not going to find it on the website.

Urban legend has it that the incident happened during Cheerfest 2014. Everywhere you looked that day there were clouds of hairspray, big bows, glittery stickers and the echoes of “Ready? Okay!” The Rutherford Rockets, with their competition time not for another four hours, decided to head out into the park to pass the time.

They had ridden Nitro, El Toro and Kingda Ka when cheer captain Lacey had the big idea of doing a selfie contest to see who could get the best on-ride picture. Despite the park’s strict no-loose-articles policy, all twelve girls piled on the Twister and kept their selfie sticks hidden until the ride had been checked and cleared for operation. When the ride reached its peak the girls whipped out their selfie sticks in preparation for the intense sequence of flips they had observed while waiting in line. Much to their surprise the ride operator initiated a new ride sequence, catching the girls off guard. As the ride began its cycle all twelve girls were impaled by their selfie sticks. As Twister continued its tumultuous tumble through the air, blood began to splatter the guests watching in horror down below.

Supposedly security officers rushed to confiscate all cell phones, cameras and recording devices to be sure that the grizzly scene was never went viral and stayed out of the press. However, rumor has it that the harnesses are now painted crimson red because no matter how hard the clean-up crew scrubbed they could never fully remove the blood spatter from the foam. If you ask team members about the tale, they will always discount it as an urban legend, much like the Stuntman’s Freefall scalping story. But true or not, better to play it safe – who would want their obituary reading “death by selfie stick?”

Minimum height requirement: 54″ to ride

For your safety, no loose articles including cell phones are permitted on Twister. All loose articles must be secured in a button or zipped pocket, locker or with a non-rider.

seasonal.name: Twister
seasonal.description: Climb onto a classic seated top-spinner if candy canes are your favorite holiday treat, then this ride is for you! This strangely epic-looking behemoth made entirely of rustic wood has only one purpose: to twist and disorient you!

rides.name: Wile E. Coyote Canyon Blaster
rides.description: A circular spin-out for junior road runners and the little coyotes who love them.

rides.name: Safari Off Road Adventure
rides.description: The ultimate safari is right in your own backyard.

rides.name: Bugaboo
rides.description: Gardeners in training will love this gently wavy tour on the back of brightly colored, spotted bug mobiles.

seasonal.name: Bugaboo
seasonal.description: Little holiday riders will love this gently wavy tour on the back of brightly colored, spotted bug mobiles.

rides.name: Bugs Bunny Camp Carousel
rides.description: Giddy up!  The ponies are ready to ride on this kid-sized carousel, scaled down for little hands and feet.

seasonal.name: Bugs Bunny Camp Carousel
seasonal.description: Giddy up!  The ponies are ready to ride on this kid-sized carousel, scaled down for little holiday riders.

rides.name: Bugs Bunny Ranger Pilots
rides.description: Fly an old timey bi-plane on this circular tour of Bugs Bunny’s favorite neighborhood!

rides.name: Sky Zooma
rides.description: Whirl through the sky for a spinning, bird’s eye view of Safari Kids! Twist faster if you dare!

rides.name: Slingshot
rides.description: Become a human slingshot as you are launched 220 feet in the sky! Additional fee required.

seasonal.name: Slingshot
seasonal.description: Become a human slingshot as you are launched 220 feet in the sky! Additional fee required.

rides.name: Saw Mill Log Flume
rides.description: Saw Mill Log Flume drops you 4 stories down into refreshing water.

rides.name: Zumanjaro: Drop of Doom
rides.description: A drop from new heights — 415 feet.

seasonal.name: Zumanjaro: Drop of Doom
seasonal.description:
A Drop From New Heights. 
Six Flags Great Adventure boasts Zumanjaro: Drop of Doom, a record-breaking drop ride featuring breathtaking views, impressive heights, astonishing speeds, stomach-tightening drops, and an adrenaline rush like no other. It is the tallest and fastest drop ride in the world, lifting riders up 415 feet in the air and rocketing back down at 90 miles per hour.

First, your eight-person gondola blasts to the top of the 415-foot structure in approximately 30 seconds. You pause for a moment to check out the aerial view of the park and anticipate the rapid heart-racing plummet coming up next. Everything soon becomes a blur as gravity pulls your gondola downwards at 90 miles per hour, reaching ground level again in less than 10 seconds — before you even have time to scream.

The three soaring Zumanjaro towers share their structure of the record-breaking Kingda Ka coaster. 

Zumanjaro: Drop of Doom was inspired by the African theme of Safari Off Road Adventure.

Are you ready to take on this all-new drop ride?

For your safety, no loose articles including cell phones are permitted on Zumanjaro. All loose articles must be secured in a button or zipped pocket, locker or with a non-rider.

rides.name: THE JOKER™
rides.description: On this free-fly coaster you'll soar in wing cars to the side of the track.

seasonal.name: THE JOKER
seasonal.description:
Six Flags Great Adventure’s 14th and most unique coaster is nothing to laugh at. After heading straight up a 12-story, 90-degree hill, this 4-D, free-fly coaster wreaks havoc as you flip head-over-heels along the weightless journey. You will experience exhilarating leaps and dives along a horizontal plane, along with unexpected drops as you tumble from one level to the next. The wing seats amp up the pandemonium since you will experience all of this chaos with no track above or below – just the sky, ground and adjacent Great Lake churning around you!

THE JOKER Facts


Massive, imposing, floating and twisting I-box track frame in a unique two-tone design
One-of-a-kind onboard magnetic technology featuring smooth head-over-heels free-fly flips providing you the feeling of weightlessness as you soar outside the confines of a traditional track
4-D wing vehicles that seat up to 8 per vehicle with a total of 5 vehicles
Face-off seats that allow you to face each other as you tumble head over heels
A 120-foot-tall, 90-degree hill that is ascended by an elevator-style, chain link lift
Two beyond 90-degree “raven” drops giving the sensation of free-falling

seasonal.description: Join the JUSTICE LEAGUE Reserve Team this holiday season to save Metropolis from THE JOKER and Lex Luthor. JUSTICE LEAGUE: Battle for Metropolis join's Holiday in the Park's attraction lineup this year as part of the newly-themed Holiday Heroes section.

rides.name: CYBORG™ Cyber Spin
rides.description: A First-of-its-Kind, 7 Story High Anti-Gravity Thrill Ride.

seasonal.name: CYBORG Cyber Spin
seasonal.description:
Six Flags Great Adventure's first-of-its-kind ride: CYBORG Cyber Spin!

This adventure, like its namesake, features state-of-the-art technology, for a thrilling anti-gravity experience like no other. 

After approaching this seven-story giant through Metropolis, you'll board a 24-seat gondola and prepare to take to the skies. As the ride raises off the ground, the ride begins to spin on all three axis independently as the movements grow larger and faster and you fly head-over-heels for an out-of-this-world ride like nothing you've ever experienced before. As the spinning slows, CYBORG brings the axis back together and lowers you back to earth.

You've now been properly trained by the teen titan himself and are ready to join the rest of the JUSTICE LEAGUE right next door on JUSTICE LEAGUE: Battle for Metropolis.

events.body:
Academic Adventures - Cyber Safari

Welcome to Cyber Safari at Six Flags Great Adventure. Bring the Wild Safari into your classroom – virtually! Students K-12 can learn about 4 units focused on adaptations, conservation, evolution, and genetics all from the safety of their current learning environment.   All virtual lessons were created by our own NJ state certified teacher and are tailored to the appropriate age groups while following the New Jersey State Learning Standards. Video and lesson plans are FREE and are easily incorporated into your classroom setting. Live animal experiences with an animal educator are available to your classroom or school and include additional teacher resources.  Give your students an opportunity to go a little Wild this Spring!

Enhance Your Adventure!

Live Lessons Let your students monkey around as you take your virtual lessons to the next level with live lessons and teacher resources! For a small upcharge, you can choose a 15 or 45 minute personalized experience for your class. Your students will have a roaring good time! Book Now

Lesson Plans

Whether you're exploring conservation efforts, or discovering Darwinian principles, you'll find the perfect lesson plan right here! View Lessons

Science on Safari

Venture out of the classroom for Science on Safari! This contact-free, naturally socially distanced experience through the Wild Safari Drive-Thru Adventure will make your students go wild. Request More Info Audio Tour

Video Resources

Check out our YouTube channel for even more engaging educational materials! View Videos

events.body:
Mark your calendar for adventure and gear up for learning!

Get out of the classroom and off of the computer with Outdoor Classroom Days this Spring! Give your students a day of fun and learning as they explore the  world's largest outdoor classroom and experience the most extraordinary thrill rides on the planet! Available Dates: April 30, May 7, May 14, May 21, May 28

FREE WORKBOOKS Available for both Physics and Middle School STEM

Our physics program has been helping kids understand and get excited about science for over 30 years! Students are encouraged to utilize one of our educational workbooks during their time at the park. Workbooks are free and can be downloaded and printed from home/school. Some activities do require the use of scientific instruments, so be sure to read through the materials list at the beginning of the packet. An added benefit of this teacher driven program is that it allows you to customize your day. Feel free to look through both packets to pick and choose what content works best for your class.  STEM Workbook Physics Workbook

Ticket Information

Get student and chaperone tickets for just $28.99 each plus tax when you order 15 or more. Best of all, you'll receive one FREE ticket for every 15 you purchase! Can't make it on one of the specified Outdoor Classroom Days? No problem! Tickets are valid for use on any operating day through September 6, 2021. Admission to Six Flags for this program is FREE for any active Season Pass or Membership Holders. Feeding your group is easy! Add on a Mega Meal Deal to your day and get one meal, one snack and a one-day drink bottle for just $19.99 plus tax! Tax Exempt? New Jersey public schools are tax exempt with payment in the form of a school check, P.O. or credit card. Private schools and schools from other states must pay New Jersey state sales tax unless a copy of a NJ ST-5 from accompanies the order. Other state and federal exemption certificates are not valid in New Jersey. Tax exemption does not apply for online orders. 

Park Reservations

Reservations are required to visit the park. If you are placing your order through the website, it will have you confirm your visit date and arrival time all within the same transaction. When ordering through the Outdoor Classroom form, a park representative will confirm your order and reservation. Tickets for our Outdoor Classroom Days must be purchased in advance and are not available at the park.

Looking for more specialized programming or catering options? We can help!

Please contact njspecialevents@sixflags.com Please note: Outdoor Classroom takes place on regular operating days when the park is open to the general public. Please check the calendar for park hours.

events.body:
Max out on thrills from March 27 - April 11!

Winter is officially gone and spring is here! Celebrate the break from school and wave goodbye to snowy weather by conquering Kingda Ka or taming the bull on El Toro. Satisfy that funnel cake craving after chomping down on a slice of pizza or kickin' barbecue wings.  We're gearing up for more days of fun and thrills than ever before, so don't miss out on all of the surprises coming your way! The best way to enjoy fun all season long is with a Memership or Season Pass! Get unlimited visits all season long, including visits to Hurrican Harbor and the Wild Safari Drive-Thru Adventure. The cun continues after Labor Day with Fright Fest, plus enjoy the warmth of the holiday season during Holiday in the Park! Tickets and Reservations will be available beginning March 16, 2021 at 12 pm. Buy Now
